Nonincrease, Decrease	#36.	 retire into the shade, hide its diminished head, fall to a low ebb, run low, languish, decay, crumble. bate, abate, dequantitate
Weakness	#160.	 drop, crumble, give way, totter, tremble, shake, halt, limp, fade, languish, decline, flag, fail, have one leg in the grave. render weak &c. adj.
Disease	#655.	 droop, flag, languish, halt
Pain	#828.	 yearn, repine, pine, droop, languish, sink
Desire	#865.	 sigh for, cry for, gape for, gasp for, pine for, pant for, languish for, yearn for, long, be on thorns for, hope for
